milestones.description: Afsar Zazai and Nasir Jamal's 104-run partnership is AFG's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 84 between Karim Sadiq and Shahzad
Samiullah Shinwari has scored 7 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for AFG breaking Mohammad Nabi's record
Calum MacLeod has scored 2 hundreds in ODIs, the most for SCOT breaking Hamilton's record
Dawlat Zadran has broken the record for most ducks (3) in ODIs for AFG, going past Shapoor's 3
Josh Davey has taken the most five-wicket hauls (1) in ODIs for SCOT, going past Gordon Goudie's record
Mohammad Nabi has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (42) for AFG, going past Samiullah Shinwari

stories.title: Javed Ahmadi and Nasir Jamal sink Scotland
stories.subTitle: Afghanistan v Scotland, Dubai Triangular Series
stories.seoTitle: Javed Ahmadi and Nasir Jamal sink Scotland
stories.summary: A strong batting display from Afghanistan's top order, powered by half-centuries from Javed Ahmadi and Nasir Jamal, helped the team to an eight-wicket victory against Scotland in Dubai
